This map is more likely to have the status of a single player than a multiplayer, since the map does not provide for either rescue of the hostages or the installation of explosives.

It is only possible to walk around the temple rooms and play classic casino games.



The map includes four full games:


 - tic-tac-toe;

 - Pinko Club;

 - Jackpot;

 - Blackjet;



The essence of creating such a map is to show that the impossible can be made possible.

In my practice of porting maps, there were many different maps where mappers tried to come up with something unusual with the help of crutches.

Why crutches, but because the CSS engine is essentially simply not adapted to create something like this.
Everything had to be done literally from Shit and Sticks.

For me, this work was just a variation of the development of my abilities in algorithmization.

I can also safely say that no one has created anything like this before me.

- Seaside is a bomb defusal map set in a decrepit port. It is a small map with water hazards. 

  Players can jump over these hazards to create shortcuts and confuse their enemies.

Lavatown

is a basic 2-16 player map themed on a town built around free-flowing lava circulation used as a source of power.

Navigate the brick alleys and cobble streets to eliminate the opposing team.

Be careful not to go for an accidental swim in the river, and please forgive the carelessly discarded cargo boxes - The fighting all broke out rather suddenly. I guess living in a caldera with the constant threat of inhaling toxic gasses, burning alive, or being boiled during a freak rainstorm has a way of stressing people out.

Good luck!

surf_embrace takes place inside a mysterious underground facility, filled with perilous obstacles, winding rooms and strange creatures. Do you have what it takes to explore such a vast and dangerous place?

This map is my sixth and final (for the foreseeable future) surf map. This project took roughly 10 months and an estimated 2000 hours, making it by far my biggest level. It is both an homage to many of the older surf maps and of my journey as a mapper, resulting in a celebration and culmination of everything this gamemode, and designing for it, has taught me. 

I want to thank everyone who was involved with the creation of the map, as it would not have been possible to release it as it is now without that crucial guidance and support. 

Hope you all enjoy this map as much as I enjoyed working on it :)

Ensure that game sounds are turned on for the definitive surf_embrace experience

de_warmblow is a port of the de_warmblow map from the Counter-Strike: Global Offensive game.

Description from the author:

About the level

This is a remake of my entry for last years GameBanana Winter Wonderland Mapping Contest. Even though I got placed 1st in the contest I was still not fully contented with the final result, what I wanted to achieve was something way more complex, beautiful and overal better, but of course that is not always possible when you have the clock ticking and pressure to release the map on schedule. So here it is, way later then I expected, but also better then I had planed, much due to lazyness, other life related stuff and lack of inspiration during some periods of time. Even before the contest had ended I already had plans to release a diferent version with warmer colors, and more pleasent to the players experience. Also because snow is fun and all, but it gets tiresome from my experience. So here it is, I bring you this map to warm your heart during the cold season _which wasn't in anyway suposed to have come out 6 months ago. #save_ It's a remake, yes, but it's also a remake that took me more time to create then every other map I've ever finished. True story. Between bug fixes including the highly request bot support, new gamemode support, new aditions, improvements, and everything else it took a lot of my time, but in the end, I got to get the most polished map I've ever gotten published. So, featuring more fun, more balanced and story telling experience, here you have it. I hope you like it, and feel that my time was worth it. For those who wondered why have I been so inactive in terms of submiting, I apreciate your attention, and apolagize for the AFKness, but I've not been totally inactive, just a bit more due to life / will to map but we all know how that is. And now that I'm at it, I'd also like to wish all of you a good Christmas season, whether you celebrate it or not. Best wishes bananites!

Special mentions

I'd like to thank some people in particular who were very supportive, kind and helpful in the making of this map. Those people are Rafael who did some modeling for me as well as some 2D art, always very kind, _Se7en_ my eternal buddy, always involved in my projects and lastly Will2k, one of the most talented mappers I know and possibly the best teacher I've ever had, without whom I would have never finished this project. \*flies away\*

Aim Levelcore is a remake of the Aim Challenge map from the Counter-Strike: Global Offensive game.

Find out how fast you can aim compared to professional players, or your friends on this custom course!

Use all your skills to set down the fastest time!

---

- The map is intended solely for internal use.

- Run the map on your local server.

- Don't turn on bots.

---

You can use the bind key to quickly restart the game.

To do this, enter the command in the game console:

bind "your_key" "mp_restartgame 1"

To restart the game early, push on the fire extinguisher.

To restart the game after completing the mission, click on the keyboard that lies on the control table.

You can use the color-coded stopwatch indicators located on the fire extinguishers:

00:00.000 - 00:30.000 | yellow light

00:30.000 - 00:40.000 | blue light

00:40.000 - 01:05.000 | green light 

01:05.000 - 10:00.000 | red ligth

FINALLY.

Started working on this 8 years ago... when I was 14, and error after error, delay after delay and massive breaks inbetween, I've finally finished it. This map should spice things up for the small number of jailbreak servers left. It's not your regular map... Trust me ;)

Features:

Armoury: M4, AWP, Deagle, Armour, Grenade, Defend The Castle.

Cellblock: Vent cell, gun cell, teleport cell, break door cell, VIP cell (with music, nade & armour), Six Chairs, gun underground

LR Room: Shot 4 Shot (+ headshot only), Gun Toss, Knife Arena (with friendly fire), 2 secrets

Pool: Mini Course, Lava Race, Sword Fight, 3 secrets

Disco: Colours, 6 songs, 2 secrets (flashing lights will be added in next version)

Football: Football, Whispers, 1 secret

Games: Football, Traitor, Deathrun, Bhop, Invisible Race, Climb (indoor + outdoor), 6 Chairs, Pool Race, Pool Course, Sword Fighting (:]), Colours, Knife Arena (LR Room), Defend The Castle (once per map)

Defend The Castle: CT's defend the castle against the T's who are trying to get in. Once T's break in, it's an instant kill on CT's. This can only be triggered once per map to avoid abuse.

Rocket: 1 incorrect input and it is locked for the rest of the round. Only smartasses who can think OUTSIDE THE BOX will be able to find the code. ;)

Epilepsy warning. The map is flooded with flashing lights and colours.

The nuke drops after 7 minutes killing everyone on the map. Stop watching porn and end the round...

MASSIVE props to Marsquakes and Fronexe for being apart of this map, giving me ideas, help and bugfixing. Thank you both <3

Next update: More games, more secrets(?), better disco, perhaps a changed layout for better map flow.

de_calamari is a port with remake of the de_calamari from the Counter-Strike: Global Offensive game.

- Story:

Phoenix Connexion has made their way into a small vacation spot in Croatia, and they need to blow up their hard drug stash the FBI is currently on them for and have closing in on their location. Their dealer, who used to operate through the Calamari Restaurant, has hidden the drugs either in some speakers and crates among a small outdoor venue, or inside the restaurant itself within a secret vault hidden under the floor tiles.

Hello.

This is a remaster of my friends 3 year old map from 2017. My friend used prefabs he downloaded randomly, and he lost the folder of them all. If you are one of the prefab creators, contact me at discord (northh#2552) and we can discuss something if you are unhappy with the uncredited usage of your prefab.

Anyway, this map features:
  • Zones
  • Forests, hills & lakes
  • Weapons
  • A loot crate
  • Houses & landmarks
  • A "church"
  • And some radios that I don't remember placing.

HOW TO PLAY

  1.  Gather some people and boot up the map.
  2.  Set mp_limitteams to 0 and mp_autoteambalance to 0 aswell.
  3.  Get everyone to join the same team, Terrorists or Counter Terrorists, doesn't matter.
  4.  (OPTIONAL) Set cl_drawhud to 0 for fun.


Special thanks to LeTexPro for making the original br_hills, and thanks to my friends for playtesting the map.
